HEADWORD: Upsitting
<hw>Up"sit`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sitting up of a
woman after her confinement, to receive and entertain her friends.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To invite your lady's <qex>upsitting</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upskip</ent>⟦br⟧
